    <h2 class="normal mb0">Above the Fog</h2>
    <p>There are some distinct benefits to being above 1400 feet in elevation. We tend to see more sunshine each day and the heat tends to be more moderate. 
    Spring starts later for us as the weather is much cooler up here in Spring and Winter. We frequently have frost pressures around the time of bud break, which can carry through into flowering. In 2008 for example, four consecutive days in April brought 19 degree temperatures and we never saw about half of our crop. Our yields average about 2 tons an acre (which is really low) but the cool, wet vintages do not have the same negative effects that come with being on the valley floor. </p> 
  </div>
</section>

